Oren Gross wrote:

&gt;Hi All
&gt;I am integrating between my junit and Ant.
&gt;So far I&#39;ve been using the regular method such as the following target:
&gt;&lt;target name=&quot;junit.test&quot; depends=&quot;init&quot; description=&quot;Run JUnit for the
&gt;AdminCenter project&quot;&gt;
&gt;	&lt;echo message=&quot;testing only the local objects!&quot;/&gt;
&gt;	&lt;echo message=&quot;testing creation of objects&quot;/&gt;
&gt;    	&lt;junit id=&quot;unit.test&quot; fork=&quot;yes&quot; haltonerror=&quot;true&quot; dir=&quot;.&quot;&gt;
&gt;      		&lt;classpath &gt;
&gt;        		&lt;path refid=&quot;project.class.path&quot;/&gt;
&gt;        		&lt;fileset dir=&quot;${ant.home}&quot;&gt;
&gt;				&lt;include name=&quot;**/*.jar&quot;/&gt;
&gt;			&lt;/fileset&gt;
&gt;      		&lt;/classpath&gt;
&gt;                &lt;jvmarg value=&quot;-Dtopaz.home=../..&quot;/&gt;
&gt;                &lt;test name=&quot;com.mercury.topaz.admincenter.app.db.AllTests&quot;
&gt;/&gt;
&gt;    	&lt;/junit&gt;
&gt;&lt;/target&gt;
&gt;
&gt;Now I want to have things for general, i.e. have it run all the &quot;AllTests&quot;
&gt;under a specific directory, i.e. do something like 
&gt;&lt;classpath&gt;
&gt;...
&gt;&lt;fileset dir=&quot;${build.dest}&quot;/&gt;
&gt;	&lt;include name=&quot;**/*AllTests.class&quot;/&gt;
&gt;&lt;/fileset&gt;
&gt;...
&gt;&lt;/classpath&gt;
&gt;...
&gt;&lt;test name=&quot;AllTests&quot;/&gt;
&gt;
&gt;How should I do that?
&gt;TIA Oren
&gt;

I probably misunderstood what you&#39;re intentions are, but does this help?

    &lt;junit haltonfailure=&quot;no&quot;&gt;
        &lt;batchtest todir=&quot;${test.results.dir}&quot; &gt;
            &lt;fileset dir=&quot;${build.dir}&quot;&gt;
                &lt;include name=&quot;**/*Test.class&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;/fileset&gt;
        &lt;/batchtest&gt;
        &lt;formatter type=&quot;xml&quot; usefile=&quot;true&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;classpath refid=&quot;project.class.path&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/junit&gt;

Mike



